; content-address-band.fk — the substrate's headline, proven on every kernel:
; intern_node is CONTENT-ADDRESSED. Two nodes of the same structural shape
; (same category, same children) intern to the SAME NodeID — so cross-document,
; cross-domain equivalence comes for free and node_eq is structural identity.
;
; The fourth kernel (fkwu) earns this through dedup in its intern arm: a fresh
; intern_node scans the live node table and returns the existing cell when the
; (category, children) shape already lives there — the C-level image of the Go
; kernel's byHash content address. Trivial interns dedup the same way, so the
; flattener's let-inlining (which re-walks a bound value at every use) keeps the
; substrate bounded instead of growing a fresh cell per re-walk.
;
; Every claim is RELATIVE or structural — never an absolute NodeID inst, which
; counts each kernel's own parse-time interns and is not portable across the
; siblings. What IS portable: same-shape identity, distinct-shape difference,
; and the projections that read a node back. Self-contained, kernel verbs only.
;
; Band verdict: 1023 when content-addressing holds across all four kernels.
;   node_eq same shape → equal                 → 1
;   node_eq different shape → not equal         → 10
;   same shape → same inst (the content address) → 100
;   different shape → different inst             → 1000
;   composite pkg is 0                           → 10000
;   type inherited from category                 → 100000
;   level inherited from category                → 1000000
;   category projects back to the field          → 10000000
;   children length is preserved                 → 100000000
;   a child's value reads back                   → 1000000000
(do
    (let FIELD (make_nodeid 1 2 99 1742))
    (defn mk-shape (val)
        (intern_node FIELD (list (intern_trivial_string "problem")
                                 (intern_trivial_string val))))
    (let a (mk-shape "ideas-need-a-pipeline"))
    (let b (mk-shape "ideas-need-a-pipeline"))   ; identical shape → same NodeID
    (let c (mk-shape "something-else"))           ; different shape → different NodeID
    (add (mul (if (node_eq a b) 1 0) 1)
    (add (mul (if (node_eq a c) 0 1) 10)
    (add (mul (if (eq (node_inst a) (node_inst b)) 1 0) 100)
    (add (mul (if (eq (node_inst a) (node_inst c)) 0 1) 1000)
    (add (mul (if (eq (node_pkg a) 0) 1 0) 10000)
    (add (mul (if (eq (node_type a) (node_type FIELD)) 1 0) 100000)
    (add (mul (if (eq (node_level a) (node_level FIELD)) 1 0) 1000000)
    (add (mul (if (node_eq (node_category a) FIELD) 1 0) 10000000)
    (add (mul (if (eq (len (node_children a)) 2) 1 0) 100000000)
         (mul (if (str_eq (node_value (head (node_children a))) "problem") 1 0) 1000000000)))))))))))
